<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06160089 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06160089 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: 'Tell the governor that we know California is a state that knowshow, and that California will show the way.  '-- Justice Allen; Broussard  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  BLACK; STATE; JUDGE; RETIREMENT; GOVERNOR; NAME  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  -- Retiring state Supreme Court Justice Allen Broussard, the court's onlyblack member, has urged Gov. Pete Wilson to appoint another black to succeedhim.;    He said only 13 states have a black justice on their highest court.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  California News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  JUDGE WANTS BLACK SUCCESSORRETIRING JUSTICEASKS WILSON TOCONTINUE TREND  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     &quot;And in the last two years, three of those 13 justices who are black haveleft the bench, and in each instance, they have been replaced by a black,&quot; hesaid.;    &quot;Tell the governor that we know California is a state that knowshow, and that California will show the way. We would ask that he consider veryfavorably the opportunity that we have to maintain that tradition.&quot;;   Broussard made the comments at a recent dinner held in his honor.;    Wilsonspokesman Franz Wisner said Friday that the governor &quot;would not name a judgesolely because of the color of one's skin. Gov. Wilson will select thehighest-quality judge possible; the individual who he thinks will do the bestjob. That may be a man or woman from any race.&quot;;    Broussard, 62, plans toretire Aug. 31, after 10 years on the court. He is the last remainingappointee of former Gov. Edmund Brown Jr. and one of two liberals on thecourt, which is dominated by five conservative appointees of former Gov.George Deukmejian.;    The court's only other black justice, Brown appointeeWiley Manuel, died in 1980.  </TEXT><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  SACRAMENTO (AP)  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910608  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3F  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  252  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday June 8, 199100160089,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>